:

$L(a(x), y) = \ln(1+e^{-ya(x)})$, $a(x)= <x, w>$

$dL(a(x), y) = d(\ln(1+e^{-ya(x)})) = \frac{d(1+e^{-y<w,x>})}{1+e^{-y<w,x>}}=\frac{e^{-y<w,x>}d(-y<w,x>)}{1+e^{-y<w,x>}} =\frac{e^{-y<w,x>}(-y)<x,dw>)}{1+e^{-y<w,x>}} = \frac{(-y)<x,dw>}{1+e^{y<w,x>}} = <-y\sigma(-ya(x))x, dw>$

, $\nabla L_w = -y\sigma(-ya(x))x$

import re
from nltk.stem.wordnet import WordNetLemmatizer

class Preprocesser:
    def __init__(self, stopwords):
        self.bad_symbol_regexp = re.compile('[^a-zA-Z0-9\s]')
        ru_lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
        def lru_lemmatizer(word):
            return ru_lemmatizer.lemmatize(word)
        self.lemmatizer = lru_lemmatizer
        self.stopwords = stopwords
        
    def __call__(self, text):
        text = text.lower()
        text = re.sub(self.bad_symbol_regexp, '', text)
        lemmas = [
            self.lemmatizer(token)
            for token in text.split()
        ]
        lemmas = [
            token
            for token in lemmas
            if token not in self.stopwords
        ]
        
        return ' '.join(lemmas)

#      step_alpha

from sklearn.metrics import balanced_accuracy_score, accuracy_score

loss_function = BinaryLogisticLoss(l2_coef=1.0)

results_alpha = []
ac_alpha = []

alpha_ = [0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 0.9, 1.0]

for step_alpha in alpha_:
    model = LinearModel(loss_function=loss_function, step_alpha=step_alpha)
    history = model.fit(X=X['train'], y=y_train, trace=True, X_val=X['valid'], y_val=y_val)
    results_alpha.append(history)

    threshold = model.get_optimal_threshold(X['valid'], y_val)
    y_pred = model.predict(X['valid'], threshold)
    accu = balanced_accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred)
    ac_alpha.append(accu)

step_alpha = 0.3
step_beta = 1.0
batch_size = 1000

for c_coef in np.logspace(-3, 2, base=2, num=6):
    loss_function = BinaryLogisticLoss(l2_coef=c_coef)

    model = LinearModel(loss_function=loss_function, step_alpha=step_alpha, step_beta=step_beta, batch_size=batch_size)
    model.fit(X=X['train'], y=y_train, trace=False)
    
    threshold = model.get_optimal_threshold(X['valid'], y_val)
    y_pred = model.predict(X['valid'], threshold)
    accuracy_value = balanced_accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred)
    print(f'{c_coef:.3f}: accuracy={accuracy_value:.3f}')
